	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for nurses in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your perfect Father, straight to the exhaustion you're carrying. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Matthew 11:28-30`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 11, text: `Come to Me, all of you who are weary and worn down, and I will give you rest. Take My yoke and learn from Me, for I am gentle and humble in heart, and you will find rest for your soul — for My yoke is easy and My burden is light, says your Father.`, note: `After a 12-hour shift with nothing left, this is your Father's standing invitation: come and be given rest.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 40:29-31`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 40, text: `I give strength to the weary, and to the one with no might I increase power. Those who wait on Me will renew their strength; they will rise up on wings like eagles, they will run and not grow weary, they will walk and not faint.`, note: `When you're running on fumes, your Father is the One who renews strength in the depleted.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 1:3-4`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 1, text: `Blessed be your Father, the Father of compassion and the God of all comfort, who comforts you in all your affliction, so that you can comfort others with the same comfort you have received from Me.`, note: `You can't pour out comfort you haven't received — let your Father comfort you first, then it overflows to your patients.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 23:1-3`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 23, text: `I am your Shepherd; you will not lack. I make you lie down in green pastures, I lead you beside still waters, I restore your soul. Even through the darkest valley, you need fear no harm, for I am with you.`, note: `You make everyone else lie down to rest — your Father makes <em>you</em> lie down and restores your soul.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 34:18`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 34, text: `I am near to the brokenhearted, and I save those who are crushed in spirit, says your Father.`, note: `When the grief of a hard loss crushes you, your Father draws nearest — not furthest — in that moment.` },
		{ ref: `Galatians 6:9`, slug: `galatians`, ch: 6, text: `Do not grow weary in doing good, for in due season you will reap a harvest, if you do not give up, says your Father.`, note: `Your faithful care matters even when no one notices — your Father sees every quiet act and it is never wasted.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 41:10`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 41, text: `Fear not, for I am with you; do not be dismayed, for I am your Father. I will strengthen you, I will help you, I will uphold you with My righteous right hand.`, note: `On the shifts where you're scared you can't do it, your Father promises to strengthen and uphold you Himself.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:6-7`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything, by prayer, bring your requests to your Father — and His peace, beyond all understanding, will guard your heart and mind.`, note: `For the anxiety you carry home from work, hand it to your Father and let His peace stand guard over your mind.` },
		{ ref: `Zephaniah 3:17`, slug: `zephaniah`, ch: 3, text: `Your Father is in your midst, a mighty one who will save; He will rejoice over you with gladness and quiet you with His love; He will sing over you.`, note: `Picture it: while you tend everyone else, your Father is quietly singing over you with delight.` },
	]}
	offersHeading={`What "our Father" offers you`}
	offersIntroHtml={`Nursing asks you to give and give until there's nothing left. Here's what your Father gives <em>you</em> instead — for free, because you're already His.`}
	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `Rest for the bone-deep weary`, bodyHtml: `You don't have to push through on empty: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/matthew/11" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">come to your Father weary and worn down</a>, and He gives you rest for your soul — the kind no day off can manufacture.` },
		{ heading: `Strength when you have none left`, bodyHtml: `When you're depleted, your Father is the One who <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/isaiah/40" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">gives strength to the weary</a> and renews the power of those who wait on Him — so you run and don't grow faint.` },
		{ heading: `Comfort that overflows to others`, bodyHtml: `Your Father is the <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/2-corinthians/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father of all comfort</a> who comforts you in your affliction — so the care you give your patients flows from comfort you've already received, not from empty.` },
		{ heading: `Nearness in the grief`, bodyHtml: `When a loss crushes you, your Father is <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/34" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">near to the brokenhearted</a>. You're not alone with the weight of what you witness — He draws closest in your hardest moments.` },
	]}
	whyHeading={`Why the Father's Heart Bible™ for nurses`}
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: `You meet God as a Father, not a rulebook`, bodyHtml: `Most Bibles can read like a list of expectations — one more thing demanding from you when you're already overdrawn. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture does — from <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Genesis 1</a> on. So instead of another voice asking more of you, you meet the One who wants to carry you.` },
		{ heading: `It's free, on your phone, with audio`, bodyHtml: `No account, no purchase, no app. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Read it free online</a> with audio on every chapter — listen on the commute home, on a break in the med room, or when you can't sleep after a hard shift. The Father's voice fits right into your real day.` },
		{ heading: `It speaks to the exhaustion you're actually facing`, bodyHtml: `Burned out? Grieving a patient? Running on empty? Start with our <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a> or learn to bring it all to Him with our <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how-to-pray guide</a> — the Word meets you right where you are.` },
