	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`You carry others through their hardest hours — but who carries you? The truth beneath every verse here, that God is before anything else a Father, is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `God tenderly invites us to believe that He is our true Father and we are His true children.`, name: `Martin Luther`, role: `the Reformer, on the opening words of the Lord's Prayer`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/b205722e3e040337b10b11b66e159abd8623472e-500x791.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Andrew Murray, George MacDonald, and Martin Luther (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel restored the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a quick hit of energy — it's a deep well, and wells fill quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father pouring something into you that the exhaustion can't drain.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I see you. I see the shift that wouldn't end, the patient you carried home in your heart, the way you give and give until there's nothing left for yourself. And I want you to hear Me over all of it: before you are a nurse, you are Mine. I love you right now — not the tireless version, not the one who never breaks. You.</p><p>You were never meant to be an endless source that no one refills. Come to Me when you're weary, and I will give you rest. Let Me carry you, so that what flows out of you to others flows from the overflow of being held by Me. You don't have to earn My care by caring for everyone else. You just have to come. I am your Father, I tend the caregiver, and I delight in you."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for nurses`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these nurses — every caregiver carrying more than anyone sees. They hold others through the worst days of their lives; would You now hold them. Let them hear Your whisper above the alarms and the exhaustion — that before they are caregivers, they are Your beloved children, tended and carried by You.</p><p>Father, give them rest for their weary souls and renew their strength when they have none left. Comfort them in the grief of every loss they witness, and heal the wounds of moral injury and compassion fatigue. Let the care they pour out flow from the overflow of Your love, not from an empty tank. Be near to them when they are brokenhearted and crushed in spirit.</p><p>I pray Your protection over them — over their bodies through long shifts, over their minds against anxiety and despair, over their hearts against bitterness and burnout. Provide for every need, surround them with people who pour back into them, and remind them that their faithful, often-unseen work is never wasted in Your sight. May they wake each day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
