		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for nurses?`, answer: `Matthew 11:28-30 (come to Me, all who are weary, and I will give you rest), Isaiah 40:29-31 (He gives strength to the weary), 2 Corinthians 1:3-4 (the Father of all comfort), Psalm 23 (He restores my soul), Psalm 34:18 (near to the brokenhearted), Galatians 6:9 (do not grow weary in doing good), and Isaiah 41:10 (I will strengthen and uphold you) all speak straight to what nurses carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about burnout and exhaustion for healthcare workers?`, answer: `Scripture takes your exhaustion seriously and offers a real place to bring it. Matthew 11:28-30 is Jesus' open invitation to the weary and worn down to come and receive rest, and Isaiah 40:29-31 promises that those who wait on God will renew their strength. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a Father who tends the caregiver — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What scripture helps with compassion fatigue and giving too much of yourself?`, answer: `2 Corinthians 1:3-4 reframes everything: God is the Father of compassion who comforts you in your affliction, so that you can comfort others with the comfort you have first received. You're not meant to be an endless source — you give from overflow. Psalm 23 reminds you that the Shepherd makes you lie down and restores your soul. Read these free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
