		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for nurses and healthcare workers?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — perfect for listening on the commute home, on a break, or when you can't sleep after a hard shift.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for nurses?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of reading one more voice demanding from you when you're already overdrawn, you meet the One who wants to carry you. For a nurse pouring out all day, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a beloved, cared-for child first, not just the one who cares for everyone else.` },
		{ question: `How can a busy nurse start reading the Bible?`, answer: `Start small and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, pick a short Psalm or a few verses, and listen to the audio while you drive home or take a break. Try a verse a day — Psalm 23, Matthew 11, or Isaiah 40 are great places to begin. Our how-to-pray guide and verses-by-topic pages can help you find words for whatever shift you just survived.` },
